pi-wayvnc-macos (1.1.0-1) unstable; urgency=low

  * Refresh bundled upstreams to tagged releases:
    - any1/wayvnc v0.10.0 (was master @ 854edbb)
    - any1/neatvnc v1.0.0 (was master @ 37e1b55)
    - any1/aml v1.0.0 (unchanged)
  * neatvnc SONAME bumped from libneatvnc.so.0 to libneatvnc.so.1.
  * postinst now restarts wayvnc.service on upgrade when the drop-in is
    enabled, so the new bundled binary takes effect immediately instead of
    waiting for a manual restart or reboot.
  * postinst now refreshes the enabled systemd drop-in from the shipped
    template on upgrade, so changes to the drop-in take effect even though
    the active file is renamed out of dpkg's tracking by the enable script.

 -- Andrian Budantsov <AndrianBdn@users.noreply.github.com>  Wed, 27 May 2026 00:00:00 +0000

pi-wayvnc-macos (1.0.0-1) unstable; urgency=low

  * Initial release.
  * Drop-in package: bundles wayvnc + libneatvnc + libaml under
    /opt/pi-wayvnc-macos/ and overrides the stock wayvnc.service via a
    systemd drop-in.
  * Adds support for VNC security type 2 (DES VNC-Auth) so macOS Screen
    Sharing can connect to wayvnc on Raspberry Pi.
  * Built from upstream any1/aml v1.0.0, any1/neatvnc master, any1/wayvnc
    master (see /opt/pi-wayvnc-macos/share/manifest.txt for pinned SHAs).

 -- Andrian Budantsov <AndrianBdn@users.noreply.github.com>  Wed, 08 Apr 2026 00:00:00 +0000
